 The President wants to expand the Executive and the Parliament by creating additional positions.It is estimated that it costs about Sh52 million to support a single Member of Parliament. According to the 2019 Census, there were 47.6 million Kenyans. The United Nations has a higher figure of 52.6 million and this variance presents a challenge to planners, analysts, and related professionals.
The Population Division of the United Nations appears to have little confidence in the government for it has continued to rely on its own projections, putting our current population at 53.8 million.



