The 70 new MP slots alone would cost enough money to recruit 56,700 teachers, nurses, doctors, and other public sector employees. In total, additional zero-sum Executive and Parliamentary baggage, including hundreds of nominated MPs could easily generated 100,000 new public sector vacancies



